org.apache.xpath.objects

Class XMLNodeCursorImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.xpath.Expression
      • org.apache.xpath.objects.XObject
        • org.apache.xpath.axes.NodeCursor
          • org.apache.xpath.objects.XMLNodeCursorImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, javax.xml.transform.SourceLocator, DTMCursorIterator, PathComponent, ExpressionNode, XPathVisitable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    XNodeSetForDOM, XNull

    public class XMLNodeCursorImpl
extends NodeCursor
    This class definition, represents an XPath 3.1 data model (XDM) ordered list of nodes that can be iterated similar to a programming language cursor (like a JDBC java.sql.ResultSet object which is cursor like, or a DB script cursor). This class, implements an XDM data model's node() abstraction. An object instance of this class, is also capable of being transformed via XSL transformation to other data types such as string. In addition to this class, Xalan-J's XSL 3 implementation also has a class org.apache.xpath.objects.ResultSequence that is capable of having an ordered list of heterogeneous XDM items (which can be of XDM types 'node', 'atomic value', 'function item', 'map' or an 'array').
    See Also:
